SIMPLE: implacable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Implacable
<hw>Im*pla"ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>implacabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>placabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>implacable</ets>. See
<er>Placable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not placable; not to be
appeased; incapable of being pacified; inexorable; <as>as, an
<ex>implacable</ex> prince</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I see thou art <qex>implacable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An object of <qex>implacable</qex> enmity.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being relieved or assuaged;
inextinguishable.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O! how I burn with <qex>implacable</qex> fire.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which wrought them pain⟦br⟧
<qex>Implacable</qex>, and many a dolorous groan.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unappeasable; inexorable; irreconcilable;
unrelenting; relentless; unyielding.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implacableness</ent>⟦br⟧
